Q1. Start by loading the IRIS dataset. [Dataset Link: Iris Flower Dataset]
A. Display the following information:
First 10 rows
Shape & Data types:
Summary statistics (mean, std, min, max)
B. Select only those rows where:
petal length > 4.5
species = "Iris-virginica"
C. Group by species and compute:
Average sepal length
Maximum petal width
Standard deviation of sepal width
D. Create a new column: "petal_ratio" petal_length/petal_width
For each species, find the average petal_ratio.

import pandas as pd
df = pd.read_csv("iris.csv")
df3=df.head(10)
df.shape
df.dtypes
df.describe()

data = df[(df["petallength"] > 4.5) & (df["species"] == "virginica")]
data
df.groupby("species").agg(
      avg_sepal_length = ("sepallength" , "mean"),
      max_sepal_length = ("petalwidth" , "max"),
      std_sepal_width = ("sepalwidth" , "std")
)
df2=df.copy()
df2["petal_ratio"] = df2["petallength"]/df2["petalwidth"]
df2.groupby("species").agg(
    {
      avg_petal_ration :=("petal_ratio","mean") 
    }
)

Q2. Start by loading the TITANIC dataset. [Dataset Link: Titanic Dataset]
A. Display only columns: Name, Sex, Age, Fare, Survived
B. Select passengers who:
Are female
Fare > 30
C. Group by Pclass and compute:
Survival rate
Average Fare
Average Age

import pandas as pd
df = pd.read_csv("titanic.csv")
dfcol=df[["name","sex","age","fare","survived"]]
dfcol
df=df[(df["sex"]=="female") & (df["fare"] > 30)]
df2=df
df2=df2.groupby('pclass').agg(
        survival_rate = ("survived","mean"),
        avg_fare = ("fare","mean"),
        avg_age = ("age","mean")
)
df2
